reviewText: This movie was obviously made on a less than shoe string budget. But it shows heart. Trina McGee gets to flex her comedic instincts in a way she was never allowed on prime time television. Its funny, entertaining and an unusual getaway.

I PURCHASED THIS MOVIE BECAUSE I THOUGHT THE IDEA OF THE DA BOOYYSHOP WOULD BE INTERESTING.  AND IM ALSO A FAN OF BOOTLEG , GHETTO MOVIES.  BUT THIS MOVIE WAS NOT GOOD.  THE ACTORS CAN'T ACT.  AND THEY HAVE BAD BODY HOES WORKING IN DA BOOTY SHOP.  NOBODY WANTS TO SEE THAT.  THE ONLY PERSON THATS GOOD IS THE LEAD ACTRESS, BUT SHE DOSENT SAVE THE MOVIE.  I WOULD NOT RECOMMENED PEOPLE TO BUY THIS, I WISH I COULD GET MY MOVEY BACK.
